      "The daily ritual of grabbing coffee often turns those disposable cups into something much more valuable for businesses - they become little loyalty boosters over time. Think about it: people who stop by their favorite spot every morning start forming connections with the brand without even realizing it. The brain basically wires itself to associate that cup of coffee with comfort and routine, making what was once an occasional purchase feel almost mandatory. Some studies back this up too. One from Harvard Business Review in 2023 found that regular contact points between customers and brands can actually boost retention rates by around 27% when compared to random encounters. So how do companies make the most of this? Well, understanding these patterns opens up all sorts of opportunities for building stronger relationships with repeat customers.",
